    <stitle>HEAT VENTILATION AIR CONDITIONING (HVAC) SYSTEM - ProStar - SYSTEM OPERATING CONTROLS - FRONT hvac SYSTEM -
        CONTROL ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl160390401" svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="1">
        <title>CONTROL ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>All major functions of the front A/C-heater system are controlled from the control panel assembly (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1603920">Figure 20</hotlnk>). It consists of three rotary knobs which electronically
            control the blower fan speed, the A/C compressor clutch, and the actuators that move the air doors used to
            control system air distribution and temperature.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1603920" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1603920.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 20. Front HVAC Control Panel Assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. BLOWER FAN SPEED CONTROL</callout1>
                <callout1>2. TEMPERATURE CONTROL</callout1>
                <callout1>3. MODE CONTROL</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
